title: Grateful Dead Live at Capitol Theater on 1976-06-17
lineage: Sony TC 153 Sony ECM 99A Mikes Master Cassette > Reel > DAT
description: Cold Rain & Snow, Big River, They Love Each Other, Cassidy, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain, Row Jimmy, Promised Land Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Samson & Delilah, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Friend Of The Devil, Let It Grow-> Drums-> Let It Grow-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around

reviews.review_text: My First Show It's not the best show I ever saw, but it was the first.  Cold Rain & Snow surprised me.  Help on the Way -> Slipnot -> Franklin's Tower delighted me.  Wharf Rat wowed me.  A special night for a new high school grad.

great show!! this is a great '76 show part of an amazing east coast run...but all other research shows scarlet begonias and the music never stopped were never played at this show........download and enjoy!!
great show great show gotta love the 70s dead

This Could Be The First Time... That's right, after listening to 11 yrs of Dead shows chronologically, from 1965 to 1976, onward, here it comes - YEAHEAH - arguably the first catcall from Bobby, in "Around and Around", the birth of another Grateful Dead tradition.

Good Times I was (unfortunately) unable to go to this show. I was too busy being born! This is the show that was the night of my birthday. Mom says I was born around 8:00 am...plenty of time to have made the gig that night! Oh well...could've been worse, I guess.
